title: Episode dated 24 December 1962
description: Opera star Rise Stevens sang traditional Christmas songs on what was essentially Johnny Carson's first Christmas show.

title: Episode dated 31 December 1962
description: New Year's Eve show that features live remote pick-ups from Times Square with Ben Grauer.

title: Episode dated 12 June 1963
description: This night's Carson show featured a live remote from the New York premiere of "Cleopatra" at the Rivoli Theatre on Broadway. The premiere portion of the show, emceed by Bert Parks, quickly turned into a debacle. Parks couldn't handle the crush of celebrities outside of the theatre, and Carson clearly enjoyed watching Parks' discomfort from the safety of his Tonight Show set back at 30 Rock.

title: Episode dated 9 November 1964
description: On this night Johnny Carson got his first network challenge in late night when ABC debuted the heavily-promoted "Les Crane Show" opposite the Tonight Show. Carson beat Crane handily in the ratings that night and every night, and Crane was taken off the air in a mere four months.

title: Episode dated 29 September 1967
description: Guests are Jack Valenti and Susan Oliver, who talks in detail about her Trans-Atlantic solo flight in a single-engine plane.

title: Episode dated 25 March 1969
description: Patrice talks about her swimming holiday, Mason Williams plays a musical saw and swaps puns with Jerry, Callas does some improbable singing impersonations and Carlin does his disc jockey routine.

title: Episode dated 14 November 1969
description: Lucy brings rehearsal footage of Johnny and Ed's guest appearance on her show, Nye plays a too cool hippie TV actor, Ozzie talks about his first break in vaudeville, and his band's first big venue.

title: Episode dated 12 December 1975
description: After an "Art Fern" Teatime movie skit, Bob shows some out takes from his upcoming Christmas special, Dean does a hilarious drunk act, and both do a number of bleeped words for comic effect. Reilly talks about problems with his boat, Carol does some quiz questions with Johnny.

title: Episode dated 3 March 1976
description: Welles talks about early radio, Byner does some hilarious impersonations imagining old film stars as doctors, then does improvisational songs where the audience picks the topics.Susan talks about her recent career, Blotner brings Johnny and Ed artwork from Costa Rica.

title: Episode dated 14 August 1981
description: Betty White, in her first TV appearance after the death of her husband Allen Ludden some two months earlier, appears as herself and as Jane to Carson's Tarzan (Tommy Newsom has a walk-on as Boy) in a comedy sketch directly parodying Bo Derek's version of "Tarzan" (1981) which had just been released and was considered one of the worst movies of all time.

title: Episode dated 3 October 1984
description: David Fuhrer demonstrates his unusual ability to speak backwards fluently.

title: Episode dated 21 May 1992
description: Robin Williams and Bette Midler were the guests. As Johnny told Bette Midler some of his favorite songs, she sang "One For My Baby (And One More For The Road)".

title: Episode dated 22 May 1992
description: May 22, 1992 was the last "Tonight Show" with Johnny Carson as host. Carson presents a retrospective of clips covering the past 30 years. Carson says goodnight for the last time.
